



1- Libraries requirement:
   - Python with .h
   - Numpy
   - Matplotlib
   - iPython
   - PIL
   - pyOpenGL
   - Nvidia SDK (optional)

2- How to compile?
   If you using your Nvidia GPU, run this into a bash shell:
   ~: make
   ~: make install

   If you do not have any Nvidia gears, you can compile without GPU support:
   ~: make -f nocuda
   ~: make install

3- How to set PATH?
   In order to call firework anyywhere from your system you have to set some PATH. If your Linux was setup with bash shell, open your .bashrc file and add:

   export FIREDIR=/home/FIREwork    <- Here you have to change according where you put FIREwork
   export PATH=$PATH:$FIREDIR/bin
   export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:$FIREDIR/lib:$FIREDIR/bin
   export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$FIREDIR/lib
   